<subSubSection id="C30C65403C0DA80CFF7F2AAD1042FF7F" box="[151,631,151,178]" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BA936CB3C0DA80CFF7F2AAD1042FF7F" blockId="4.[151,631,151,178]" box="[151,631,151,178]" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">
<heading id="D0E181A73C0DA80CFF7F2AAD1042FF7F" bold="true" box="[151,631,151,178]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B962EAD93C0DA80CFF7F2AAD1042FF7F" bold="true" box="[151,631,151,178]" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D483C0DA80CFF062AAD1042FF7F" authority="Whitley, 1930, p. 251" authorityName="Whitley" authorityPageNumber="251" authorityYear="1930" box="[238,631,151,178]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mugilidae" genus="Ellochelon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mugiliformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B962EAD93C0DA80CFF062AAD1347FF7C" bold="true" box="[238,370,151,178]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">Ellochelon</emphasis>
Whitley, 1930, p.251
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30C65403C0DA80CFF7F2AE51387FE1F" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA936CB3C0DA80CFF7F2AE51387FE1F" blockId="4.[151,1437,223,646]" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis id="B962EAD93C0DA80CFF7F2AE51327FF37" bold="true" box="[151,274,223,249]" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Robust body, deep caudal peduncle. Head flat and broad. Terminal mouth. Lips thin and without any fleshy lamellae on lower jaw. Adipose eye fold absent. Maxilla curved downwards and visible postero-ventrally when mouth closed. Nostrils nearer to each other than to eye or lip. Scales are weakly ctenoid and fewer than 
<quantity id="4CEE9B2E3C0DA80CFA8C2B1D17A8FE8F" box="[1380,1437,295,321]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.112" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" unit="in" value="28.0">28 in</quantity>
lateral series. Pectoral axillary scale absent. Pectoral fin blackish with yellow margin. Anal fin contains 3 spines and 8 soft rays. Truncated caudal fin. Yellowish iris. Body dorsally olive brown, flanks silvery, pale yellowish abdomen, fins dusky. About 6 dark stripes on lateral series longitudinally. 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D483C0DA80CFC8F2BA911D5FE63" authorityName="Whitley" authorityYear="1930" box="[871,992,403,429]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mugilidae" genus="Ellochelon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mugiliformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B962EAD93C0DA80CFC8F2BA911D5FE63" box="[871,992,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">Ellochelon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is monotypic Genus and is represented by 
<emphasis id="B962EAD93C0DA80CFF522B8D1387FE1F" box="[186,434,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">
<taxonomicName id="4C164D483C0DA80CFF522B8D139AFE1F" baseAuthorityName="Quoy &amp; Gaimard" baseAuthorityYear="1825" box="[186,431,439,465]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mugilidae" genus="Ellochelon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mugiliformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vaigiensis">Ellochelon vaigiensis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30C65403C0DA80CFF2F2BE11115FD4B" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA936CB3C0DA80CFF2F2BE11115FD4B" blockId="4.[151,1437,223,646]" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis id="B962EAD93C0DA80CFF2F2BE1130EFE3B" bold="true" box="[199,315,475,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C164D483C0DA80CFEA92BE1105EFE3B" authority="Whitley (1930)" authorityName="Whitley" authorityYear="1930" box="[321,619,475,501]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mugilidae" genus="Ellochelon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mugiliformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B962EAD93C0DA80CFEA92BE1138FFE3B" box="[321,442,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">Ellochelon</emphasis>
Whitley (1930)
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<emphasis id="B962EAD93C0DA80CFC7D2BE111D9FE3B" box="[917,1004,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">Planiliz</emphasis>
a by its truncate caudal fin, broad head, fewer number of longitudinal scales, distinct stripes on lateral scales and darker fins. Some authors like Schultz (1953), 
<bibRefCitation id="EF874B3A3C0DA80CFF18281E13A5FDF0" author="Munro, I. S. R." box="[240,400,547,574]" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" pagination="15 - 18" refId="ref12980" refString="Munro, I. S. R. (1956) Handbook of Australian Fishes. No. 6. Fisheries newsletter Sydney, 15 (12), 15 - 18" type="journal article" year="1956">Munro (1956)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF874B3A3C0DA80CFE7328191078FDF0" author="Thomson, J. M." box="[411,589,547,574]" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" pagination="70 - 131" refId="ref13558" refString="Thomson, J. M. (1954) The Mugilidae of Australia and adjacent seas. Australian Journal of Marine and Freshwater Research, 5, 70 - 131." type="journal article" year="1954">Thomson (1954</bibRefCitation>
&amp; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF874B3A3C0DA80CFD9928191098FDF3" author="Thomson, J. M." box="[625,685,547,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" pagination="457 - 562" refId="ref13589" refString="Thomson, J. M. (1997) The Mugilidae of the world. Memoirs of the Queensland Museum, 41 (3), 457 - 562." type="journal article" year="1997">1997</bibRefCitation>
), 
<bibRefCitation id="EF874B3A3C0DA80CFD2828191160FDF0" author="Pillay, S. R." box="[704,853,547,574]" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" pagination="547 - 576" refId="ref13088" refString="Pillay, S. R. (1962) A revision of Indian Mugilidae, Journal of Bombay Natural History Society, 59 (1 &amp; 2), 254 - 170 &amp; 547 - 576." type="journal article" year="1962">Pillay (1962)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF874B3A3C0DA80CFC8928191676FDF3" author="Masuda, H. &amp; Amaoka, K. &amp; Araga, C. &amp; Uyeno, T. &amp; Yoshino, T." box="[865,1091,547,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" refId="ref12911" refString="Masuda, H., Amaoka, K., Araga, C., Uyeno, T. &amp; Yoshino, T. (1984) The fishes of the Japanese Archipelago. Vol. 1. Tokai University Press, Tokyo, 437 pp." type="book" year="1984">
Masuda 
<emphasis id="B962EAD93C0DA80CFC29281E11C7FDF3" box="[961,1010,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">et al</emphasis>
(1984)
</bibRefCitation>
recognized it as 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D483C0DA80CFAE928191706FDF3" authorityName="D.S.Jordan &amp; J.Swain" authorityYear="1884" box="[1281,1331,547,573]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mugilidae" genus="Liza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mugiliformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Liza</taxonomicName>
whereas, Fowler (1944), 
<bibRefCitation id="EF874B3A3C0DA80CFEAF287D13EBFDAF" author="Smith, J. L. B." box="[327,478,583,609]" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" pagination="833 - 843" refId="ref13518" refString="Smith, J. L. B. (1948) A generic revision of the mugilid fishes of South Africa. Annual Magazine of Natural History, South Africa, 11 (14), 833 - 843." type="journal article" year="1948">Smith (1948)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF874B3A3C0DA80CFE02287D10BCFDAC" author="Randall, J. E." box="[490,649,583,610]" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" pagination="1 - 243" refId="ref13309" refString="Randall, J. E. (1955) Fishes of the Gilbert Islands. Atoll Research Bulletin, 47, 1 - 243. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00775630.47.1" type="journal article" year="1955">Randall (1955</bibRefCitation>
&amp; 1959), 
<bibRefCitation id="EF874B3A3C0DA80CFD16287D11DAFDAF" author="Ghasemzadeh, J." box="[766,1007,583,609]" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" refId="ref12468" refString="Ghasemzadeh, J. (1998) Phylogeny and Systematics of Indo-Pacific mullets (Teleostei: Mugilidae) with special reference to the mullets of Australia. Ph. D. Dissertation. Macquarie University, Sydney, 397 pp." type="book" year="1998">Ghasemzadeh (1998)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF874B3A3C0DA80CFC13287D1696FDAF" author="Durand, J. D. &amp; Chen, W. J. &amp; Shen, K. N. &amp; Fu, C. &amp; Borsa, P." box="[1019,1187,583,609]" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" pagination="73 - 92" refId="ref12096" refString="Durand, J. D., Chen, W. J., Shen, K. N., Fu, C. &amp; Borsa, P. (2012 a) Genus level taxonomic changes implied by the mitochondrial phylogeny of grey mullets (Teleostei: Mugiliformes: Mugilidae) molecular phylogenetic evidence challenges two centuries of morphology- based taxonomic studies. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 64, 73 - 92. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2012.03.006" type="journal article" year="2012">Durand (2012)</bibRefCitation>
, Eschmeyer and Fong (2015) recognized 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D483C0DA80CFE83285113D1FD4B" authorityName="Whitley" authorityYear="1930" box="[363,484,619,645]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mugilidae" genus="Ellochelon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mugiliformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B962EAD93C0DA80CFE83285113D1FD4B" box="[363,484,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">Ellochelon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as distinct and valid Genus.
</paragraph>
